## Appendix

### Database Schema Reference
```sql
-- Existing tables leveraged by this feature
users (id, telegram_id, first_name, is_admin, is_approved)
collaborations (id, creator_id, collab_type, status, created_at)
requests (id, collaboration_id, requester_id, host_id, status)
notification_preferences (user_id, notifications_enabled)
```

### API Endpoints Referenced
```
GET /api/collaborations (filtered for recent active)
POST /api/requests (for direct collaboration requests)
```

### Telegram Bot Commands
```
/newcollab - Initiate collab broadcast (admin only)
/cancel - Cancel current broadcast session
```

This comprehensive PRD serves as the complete blueprint for implementing the New Collab Broadcast feature, covering all aspects from user experience to technical implementation details.